title: Remote - Online Data Analyst (English speakers)
description:
Are you a detail-oriented individual with a passion for research and a good understanding of national and local geography? This freelance opportunity allows you to work at your own pace and from the comfort of your own home.
 A Day in the Life of an Online Data Analyst:
In this role, you will be working on a project aimed at enhancing the content and quality of digital maps that are used by millions of people worldwide
Completing research and evaluation tasks in a web-based environment such as verifying and comparing data, and determining the relevance and accuracy of information.
 Description and Requirements
 No previous professional experience is required to apply to this role, however, working on this project will require you to pass the basic requirements and go through a standard assessment process. This is a part-time long-term project and your work will be subject to our standard quality assurance checks during the term of this agreement.
 Basic Requirements
Full Professional Proficiency in English language
Being a resident in Australia for the last 2 consecutive years and having familiarity with current and historical business, media, sport, news, social media, and cultural affairs in Australia.
Ability to follow guidelines and conduct online research using search engines, online maps, and website information
Flexibility to work across a diverse set of task types, including maps, news, audio tasks, and relevance
Daily access to a broadband internet connection, computer, and relevant software
 Assessment
In order to be hired into the program, you’ll take an open book qualification exam that will determine your suitability for the position and complete ID verification. Our team will provide you with guidelines and learning materials before your qualification exam. You will be required to complete the exam in a specific timeframe but at your convenience.
 Equal Opportunity
All qualified applicants will receive consideration for a contractual relationship without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, or protected veteran status. At TELUS Digital AI, we are proud to offer equal opportunities and are committed to creating a diverse and inclusive community. All aspects of selection are based on applicants’ qualifications, merits, competence, and performance without regard to any characteristic related to diversity.

title: AI Specialist
description:
Position Description: AI Specialist
Location: Melbourne, VIC, Australia
Employment Type: Full-Time, Permanent
Salary: TBC
Applications Close: July 17, 2025
Company: Tasman Logistics Services Pty Ltd
Website: www.taslog.com.au
About Tasman Logistics Services
Tasman Logistics Services is Australia’s premier logistics leading the charge in global supply chain innovation. From our cutting-edge Control Tower to our new Supersite, we’re transforming logistics for our clients with AI-driven solutions, sustainability, and unmatched reliability. We are obsessed with being the best and the next part of our journey to greatness is to be a leader in Tech and AI. Join us to redefine the future of logistics and become part of a team driving $1B in revenue by 2030!
 The Opportunity
We’re seeking an AI Specialist to accelerate our AI-driven transformation, enhancing our Tasman Control Tower and delivering world-class solutions for our operations and clients. You’ll develop AI and machine learning tools to optimize freight, boost customer engagement, and support our sustainability goals, contributing to new revenue and 20% waste reduction. If you’re passionate about AI, logistics, and making a global impact, this is your chance to thrive in a high-growth, tech-forward environment.
 Key Responsibilities
Develop AI Solutions: Build and deploy machine learning models (e.g., predictive analytics, dynamic routing) to enhance the Control Tower, optimising Tasman’s large fleet and warehousing operations
Support Customer Acquisition: Create AI-driven tools (e.g., chatbots, customer journey mapping) to personalize onboarding and pricing
Enhance Customer Retention: Implement predictive churn models and tailored analytics dashboards, reducing churn
Optimize Client Supply Chains: Use AI to deliver cost savings
Improve Operations: Apply AI to predictive maintenance and resource allocation, cutting operational costs and supporting global expansion
Collaborate with Tech Team: Work with AI, IoT, blockchain, and analytics specialists to integrate AI tools, ensuring scalability and innovation.
Support ESG Goals: Develop AI-driven sustainability metrics (e.g., 20% emissions reduction) aligning with Tasman’s and clients’ net-zero targets
 Skills and Experience
Essential:
Bachelor’s/Master’s in Computer Science, Data Science, AI, or related field.
3+ years in AI/ML development
Proficiency in ML frameworks (e.g., Python, TensorFlow, PyTorch) and cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, Azure).
Experience with real-time data processing (e.g., IoT, APIs) and analytics tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI).
Strong problem-solving and communication skills to collaborate with clients and teams.
Desirable:
Knowledge of logistics KPIs (e.g., DIFOT, cost per shipment) and ESG metrics (e.g. CO2 emissions).
Familiarity with NLP, IoT, or blockchain in supply chain applications (May 8, 2025).
Why Join Tasman?
Impact: Contribute to new revenue helping Tasman achieve a $1B+ global vision by 2030.
Innovation: Develop AI solutions with our Control Tower and Supersite, leading the logistics industry
Growth: Join a large team with global opportunities
Rewards: Competitive salary, performance bonuses, and career growth in a tech-driven company.
Culture: Work under CEO Ivan Vanis and his highly driven and hungry team in a bold, visionary environment, passionate about excellence and sustainability

title: AI Smart Search Specialist
description:
About The Team
The Website Strategy and Management team of approximately 10 website strategy and functionality experts is located across multiple sites, primarily in Brisbane and Newcastle. The team manages the departments websites and website projects and facilitates better website user experiences for clients and staff through the provision of platform and content strategy, governance and guidance. We identify and prioritise improvements, delivering iterative enhancements by driving innovation in our platforms.
The AI Smart Search specialist will:
enhance how users discover content and services by leveraging machine learning (ML), natural language processing (NLP), and artificial intelligence (AI)
lead the development and optimisation of intelligent search experiences within our Digital Experience Platform (DXP), including the Coveo Generative AI Proof of Concept
ensure our DXP search capabilities are fast, relevant, and adaptive, while also exploring personalisation to elevate client engagement and drive digital experiences across channels

Their focus will be on optimising the search experience driven by our Digital Experience Platform (DXP), including:
Capability Uplift: Elevate our search and analytics function by integrating advanced search capabilities.
Website User Experience Enhancement: Improve the overall user experience by ensuring that the department's website's AI smart search experience is ethical, meets user needs, accurate and robust
Content Discoverability: Enhance the discoverability of content across external and internal search tools by optimising legacy search systems and integrating advanced/emerging search technologies, ensuring content remains findable and usable.

Our Ideal Candidate will have:
The AI Smart Search specialist will demonstrate expertise in the AI Smart Search field and have the ability to
Directly support the department's Website Strategy and Management team in a Website AI Smart Search Proof of Concept using Coveo Relevance Generative Answering.
Understand website user needs and perform data analysis to uncover patterns, behaviours and insights that can inform areas of improvement with our search experience (internal and external)
Develop and implement AI powered learning models for the website.
Fine tune/improve search response to ensure user queries are understood, relevant information is returned/presented, and results rank effectively.
Develop processes and procedure steps to capture what and how we do things within the system.
Form a baseline of current search experiences that can be used to assess AI Smart Search POC outcomes.
Develop measurement frameworks/metrics that can be used to evaluate and track AI performance.

The worker will participate in knowledge/skills transfer activities as part of this engagement.


To be considered for the role click the 'apply' button or for more information about this and other opportunities please contact Muhammad Warsi on (0)2 6151 9201 or email: mwarsi@paxus.com.au and quote the above job reference number.
Paxus values diversity and welcomes applications from Indigenous Australians, people from diverse cultural and linguistic backgrounds and people living with a disability. If you require an adjustment to the recruitment process, including the application form in an alternate format, please contact me on the above contact details.

title: Data & AI Consultant - Multiple Positions
description:

Competitive Salary Package - Permanent Opportunities
Multiple Roles and Opportunities

What We're Looking For:
We're seeking Data Scientists, Machine Learning Engineers, AI Researchers, and Data Engineers who are ready to tackle complex challenges and drive meaningful change through data-driven solutions



Your Role May Involve:

Our Client

It works with many different industries to solve problems and find better ways of doing things. Using new technology and smart ideas, the company supports its clients in becoming more efficient and successful. With teams around the world, it brings together experts who understand both business and technology.



Interested?
Talented, committed, can-do individuals have always been the cornerstone of this dynamic organisation. If you have what it takes to thrive in this role and want to know more, please apply and a team member will be in touch



Privacy

title: AI Analyst
description:
About Us

Founded in 2001, we set out to simplify the complexities of wealth management. We support leading institutions and private wealth firms with cutting-edge technology and outstanding service. We offer the only fully integrated investment platform that enables comprehensive management of an investor’s entire portfolio in one place. Join us on our mission to redefine and evolve effective wealth management.

The Role

As our AI Analyst, you will shape and deliver our inaugural Artificial Intelligence strategy. Working closely with the Head of Corporate Applications and the wider business, you will contribute to the sourcing, design, implementation and support of AI and Machine Learning solutions across internal and client-facing operations.
  
Your efforts will support both vendor-provided and internally developed AI technologies, enhancing operational efficiency and aligning with the business's broader strategic goals.
  
This role is central to integrating AI into our processes, identifying high-value use cases and ensuring the adoption is smooth and impactful.
  
Key Responsibilities
Analyse and map existing workflows to identify pain points and areas for automation.
Collaborate with internal teams and external vendors to design and integrate AI models including ML, NLP, and data analysis tools.
Propose enhancements using generative AI and data-led solutions.
Recommend and implement fit-for-purpose AI tools.
Desired Qualifications, Experience and Competencies
Certifications in AI product management or machine learning.
Hands-on experience with data integration, transformation, and storage.
Experience with Azure technologies including Cognitive Services, Machine Learning, Data Factory, and Microsoft Co-pilot.
Proven experience launching AI-powered products from concept to deployment is highly desirable.
Strong interest and foundational knowledge in AI concepts (ML, deep learning, NLP).
What We Offer
Flexible hybrid work environment—split your time between home (3 days) and the office (2 days).
Competitive salary with variable annual performance bonus incentive of up to 20%.
A chance to impart your knowledge in this new, evolving specialist field.
Comprehensive leave benefits, including paid parental leave and purchased leave options.
Access to novated leasing and financial wellness courses.
Professional development opportunities tailored to your growth.
End-of-trip facilities at 367 Collins Street, Melbourne.
How to Apply

Please apply with your CV and cover letter detailing how your capabilities and career interests align with the key responsibilities and competencies of this role.

We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workforce and welcome applications from all qualified candidates.

Please Note: Only applicants with full, unrestricted work rights in Australia will be considered. A police check will be required for successful candidates.
